Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.13,0:00:05.49,English,,0000,0000,0000,,Someday we’ll shatter the chains of gravity
Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.49,0:00:11.23,English,,0000,0000,0000,,and I’ll take you along, like a satellite
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.85,0:00:30.44,English,,0000,0000,0000,,I came to that city, searching for you,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.44,0:00:34.52,English,,0000,0000,0000,,and wandering the streets at night
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.52,0:00:38.17,English,,0000,0000,0000,,The voice I heard in the receiver
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.17,0:00:42.23,English,,0000,0000,0000,,For some reason, I can’t get it off my mind
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.23,0:00:45.84,English,,0000,0000,0000,,When I found you, your eyes were red
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.84,0:00:49.67,English,,0000,0000,0000,,Discarding any pretense that you were fine
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.67,0:00:52.54,English,,0000,0000,0000,,There’s no way I could stand back and let
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.54,0:00:56.87,English,,0000,0000,0000,,you sink into that inky marsh
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.87,0:01:01.33,English,,0000,0000,0000,,Someday we’ll break free from the chains of gravity
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.33,0:01:04.26,English,,0000,0000,0000,,and fly to space, like a satellite
Dialogue: 0,0:01:04.26,0:01:09.09,English,,0000,0000,0000,,Once we’re there, even our bodies will weigh
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.09,0:01:11.96,English,,0000,0000,0000,,1/6
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.96,0:01:15.56,English,,0000,0000,0000,,I’d be happy if the sorrow that burdens you
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.56,0:01:19.64,English,,0000,0000,0000,,could be lightened, even just a bit
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.64,0:01:23.00,English,,0000,0000,0000,,Someday I’ll take you
Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.00,0:01:26.83,English,,0000,0000,0000,,and we’ll go there
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.83,0:01:32.23,English,,0000,0000,0000,,Beyond the reach of gravity
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.97,0:01:39.61,English,,0000,0000,0000,,We may not be able to take a vacation to space,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.61,0:01:43.66,English,,0000,0000,0000,,but let’s go somewhere that’s physically high
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.66,0:01:47.26,English,,0000,0000,0000,,I gave it a lot of thought and decided
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.26,0:01:51.36,English,,0000,0000,0000,,on the red tower at the harbor
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.36,0:01:53.99,English,,0000,0000,0000,,I pretended I’d come running there
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.99,0:01:58.78,English,,0000,0000,0000,,to hide the fast beating of my heart
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.78,0:02:02.63,English,,0000,0000,0000,,Today I’ll earn the right to take your hand
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.63,0:02:05.99,English,,0000,0000,0000,,and rescue you
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.99,0:02:09.35,English,,0000,0000,0000,,Just like a space elevator,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.35,0:02:13.42,English,,0000,0000,0000,,we’ll pierce through the clouds, like a satellite
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.42,0:02:16.99,English,,0000,0000,0000,,Once we’ve risen 300 meters,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.99,0:02:21.10,English,,0000,0000,0000,,perhaps we’ll be a bit lighter
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.10,0:02:24.70,English,,0000,0000,0000,,In short, this is just child’s play
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.70,0:02:28.76,English,,0000,0000,0000,,but I want you to understand, even slightly, what it means
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.76,0:02:35.94,English,,0000,0000,0000,,I want to take you even higher above the Earth’s surface
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.94,0:02:41.25,English,,0000,0000,0000,,Beyond the reach of gravity
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.07,0:02:55.44,English,,0000,0000,0000,,My feelings play a shy game of hide-and-seek,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.44,0:02:59.48,English,,0000,0000,0000,,but you’ve probably found them all already
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.48,0:03:04.38,English,,0000,0000,0000,,But more so than that, saving you
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.38,0:03:07.18,English,,0000,0000,0000,,is my one selfish desire
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.18,0:03:10.76,English,,0000,0000,0000,,By borrowing the strength of the Sun
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.76,0:03:14.86,English,,0000,0000,0000,,the Moon glows a brilliant white
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.86,0:03:22.77,English,,0000,0000,0000,,Won’t you rely on me in the same way?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.77,0:03:27.09,English,,0000,0000,0000,,Someday we’ll shatter the chains of gravity
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.09,0:03:30.19,English,,0000,0000,0000,,and I’ll take you along, like a satellite
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.19,0:03:35.50,English,,0000,0000,0000,,Then all the pain and sadness will weigh
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.50,0:03:37.90,English,,0000,0000,0000,,1/6
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.90,0:03:41.47,English,,0000,0000,0000,,Star ships still lie far in the future,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.47,0:03:45.57,English,,0000,0000,0000,,but until we reach that time,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.57,0:03:48.23,English,,0000,0000,0000,,won’t you take my left hand
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.23,0:03:51.59,English,,0000,0000,0000,,and hold it tight?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.59,0:03:52.75,English,,0000,0000,0000,,Someday
